olive oil
1 carrot
1 parsnip
1 celery
1 Brown Onion
1 packet beef & pork mince
1 sachet Herb & Mushroom Seasoning
1 packet Worcestershire sauce
1 sachet Grated Parmesan Cheese
1 cup boiling water
30 g butter
1 packet filo pastry
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Cut
carrot and parsnip into bite-sized chunks.
• Place veggies in a baking dish. Drizzle with olive
oil, season with salt and toss to coat.
• Roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.

Little cooks: Help with tossing the veggies!

• Meanwhile, roughly chop celery and onion. Boil
the kettle.

• When veggies have 10 minutes remaining, heat
a large frying pan over high with a drizzle of olive
oil. Cook beef & pork mince, breaking up with a
spoon, until just browned, 2-3 minutes.
• Cook celery and onion, stirring, until softened,
4-6 minutes.
• Add herb & mushroom seasoning and cook,
stirring, until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Remove pan from heat, then add Worcestershire
sauce, gravy granules and the boiling water
(1 cup for 2 people / 2 cups for 4 people), then stir
to combine. Season to taste.

• Reduce oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced.
• Transfer mince mixture to the baking dish with
the roasted veggies. Stir to combine.

• In a small heatproof bowl, add the butter and
microwave in 10 second bursts until melted.
• Lightly scrunch each sheet of filo pastry and
place on top of mince mixture to completely
cover.
• Gently brush melted butter over to coat.
• Bake pie until golden, 15-20 minutes.
• In the last 10 minutes of bake time, sprinkle over
shredded Cheddar cheese, return dish to oven
and continue baking.

Little cooks: Kids can help scrunch the filo pastry.

• Divide gravy beef, pork and veggie filo pie
between plates. Enjoy!